This paper is about cross-domain image generation using deep generative models, which is a popular research topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework involves the use of adversarial loss, which is a common technique in generative models and can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the exploration of latent spaces, which is a technique used in graph theory (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
